{"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.NormedSpace.Star.ContinuousFunctionalCalculus","instances":[{"typeNames":["Subtype","Membership.mem","StarSubalgebra","CommRing.toCommSemiring","Ring.toSemiring","NormedRing.toRing","SetLike.instMembership","StarSubalgebra.setLike","elementalStarAlgebra","UniformSpace.toTopologicalSpace","PseudoMetricSpace.toUniformSpace","SeminormedRing.toPseudoMetricSpace","NormedRing.toSeminormedRing","TopologicalRing.toTopologicalSemiring","NonAssocRing.toNonUnitalNonAssocRing","Ring.toNonAssocRing","semi_normed_top_ring","NonUnitalNormedRing.toNonUnitalSeminormedRing","NormedRing.toNonUnitalNormedRing"],"name":"instNormedCommRingSubtypeMemStarSubalgebraToCommSemiringToSemiringToRingInstMembershipSetLikeElementalStarAlgebraToTopologicalSpaceToUniformSpaceToPseudoMetricSpaceToSeminormedRingToTopologicalSemiringToNonUnitalNonAssocRingToNonAssocRingSemi_normed_top_ringToNonUnitalSeminormedRingToNonUnitalNormedRing","className":"NormedCommRing"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.NormedSpace.Star.GelfandDuality","Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.StarSubalgebra"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L284-L287","name":"continuousFunctionalCalculus_map_id","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#continuousFunctionalCalculus_map_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L278-L281","name":"continuousFunctionalCalculus","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#continuousFunctionalCalculus","doc":"**Continuous functional calculus.** Given a normal element `a : A` of a unital C⋆-algebra,\nthe continuous functional calculus is a `StarAlgEquiv` from the complex-valued continuous\nfunctions on the spectrum of `a` to the unital C⋆-subalgebra generated by `a`. Moreover, this\nequivalence identifies `(ContinuousMap.id ℂ).restrict (spectrum ℂ a))` with `a`; see\n`continuousFunctionalCalculus_map_id`. As such it extends the polynomial functional calculus. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L263-L268","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceHomeo","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceHomeo","doc":"The homeomorphism between the character space of the unital C⋆-subalgebra generated by a\nsingle normal element `a : A` and `spectrum ℂ a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L244-L256","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.bijective_characterSpaceToSpectrum","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.bijective_characterSpaceToSpectrum","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L238-L241","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.continuous_characterSpaceToSpectrum","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.continuous_characterSpaceToSpectrum","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L229-L235","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceToSpectrum","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceToSpectrum","doc":"The natural map from `characterSpace ℂ (elementalStarAlgebra ℂ x)` to `spectrum ℂ x` given\nby evaluating `φ` at `x`. This is essentially just evaluation of the `gelfandTransform` of `x`,\nbut because we want something in `spectrum ℂ x`, as opposed to\n`spectrum ℂ ⟨x, elementalStarAlgebra.self_mem ℂ x⟩` there is slightly more work to do. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L228-L228","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceToSpectrum_coe","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.characterSpaceToSpectrum_coe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L217-L219","name":"StarSubalgebra.spectrum_eq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#StarSubalgebra.spectrum_eq","doc":"**Spectral permanence.** The spectrum of an element is invariant of the (closed)\n`StarSubalgebra` in which it is contained. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L210-L212","name":"StarSubalgebra.mem_spectrum_iff","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#StarSubalgebra.mem_spectrum_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L202-L207","name":"StarSubalgebra.coe_isUnit","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#StarSubalgebra.coe_isUnit","doc":"For a unital C⋆-subalgebra `S` of `A` and `x : S`, if `↑x : A` is invertible in `A`, then\n`x` is invertible in `S`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L185-L197","name":"StarSubalgebra.isUnit_coe_inv_mem","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#StarSubalgebra.isUnit_coe_inv_mem","doc":"For `x : A` which is invertible in `A`, the inverse lies in any unital C⋆-subalgebra `S`\ncontaining `x`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L109-L180","name":"elementalStarAlgebra.isUnit_of_isUnit_of_isStarNormal","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#elementalStarAlgebra.isUnit_of_isUnit_of_isStarNormal","doc":"This is the key lemma on the way to establishing spectral permanence for C⋆-algebras, which is\nestablished in `StarSubalgebra.spectrum_eq`. This lemma is superseded by\n`StarSubalgebra.coe_isUnit`, which does not require an `IsStarNormal` hypothesis and holds for\nany closed star subalgebra. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L85-L100","name":"spectrum_star_mul_self_of_isStarNormal","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#spectrum_star_mul_self_of_isStarNormal","doc":"This lemma is used in the proof of `elementalStarAlgebra.isUnit_of_isUnit_of_isStarNormal`,\nwhich in turn is the key to spectral permanence `StarSubalgebra.spectrum_eq`, which is itself\nnecessary for the continuous functional calculus. Using the continuous functional calculus, this\nlemma can be superseded by one that omits the `IsStarNormal` hypothesis. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.lean#L70-L74","name":"instNormedCommRingSubtypeMemStarSubalgebraToCommSemiringToSemiringToRingInstMembershipSetLikeElementalStarAlgebraToTopologicalSpaceToUniformSpaceToPseudoMetricSpaceToSeminormedRingToTopologicalSemiringToNonUnitalNonAssocRingToNonAssocRingSemi_normed_top_ringToNonUnitalSeminormedRingToNonUnitalNormedRing","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/NormedSpace/Star/ContinuousFunctionalCalculus.html#instNormedCommRingSubtypeMemStarSubalgebraToCommSemiringToSemiringToRingInstMembershipSetLikeElementalStarAlgebraToTopologicalSpaceToUniformSpaceToPseudoMetricSpaceToSeminormedRingToTopologicalSemiringToNonUnitalNonAssocRingToNonAssocRingSemi_normed_top_ringToNonUnitalSeminormedRingToNonUnitalNormedRing","doc":""}]}